               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Āʾīn-i Akbarī by ʿAllāmī Shaykh Abū al-Faz̤l Nāgawrī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064913 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115922 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85135483" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1555x-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar ur">Persian, Arabic, Urdu</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20881">Āʾīn-i Akbarī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20881">آئين اكبرى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Complete copy of the compendious gazetteer <title key="work_20881">Āʾīn-i Akbarī</title>, the last volume of the official regnal chronicle, the <title key="work_20881">Akbar'nāmah</title>, by <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658503.0x000001 viaf_5150639" role="aut">ʿAllāmī Shaykh Abū al-Faz̤l Nāgawrī</persName>, commissioned by the Timurid (Mughal) ruler, <persName key="viaf_3264079" role="pat">Emperor Akbar I</persName> (d. 1014/1605). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work comprises an introduction, three sections termed daftar, and a conclusion containing the author’s partial autobiography. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Painted illustrations (ff. 36v, 37v, 69r, 69v, 284v, 285r). 
</p>
                        <p>Diagrams and tables (ff. 11v-12r, 16r-18v, 20r. 20v-22r, 25r-26v, 30v-32v, 35v-36r, 55v-57r, 71r-74v,75v-76r, 83v-84r, 88v-89r, 97v-127v, 130v-142v, 145r-147r, 148r-153r, 154v-159r, 160r-164v, 166v, 168r-172r, 172v, 173, 175r-178v, 181r-183v, 186r-190r, 191r, 194v-198v, 199r-201r, 202v-203v, 207v-209v, 213v-214r, 216r, 225r, 225v-232v, 235r, 235v, 238r, 257). 
</p>
                        <p>Scribal nastaʿlīq occasionally lapsing into shikastah āmīz, on oriental papers occasionally tinted pale blue. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations, occasionally dense. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Original covers lost. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound; cropped, creased, stained, wormholes, later repairs. 
</p>
                        <p>Condition fragile. 
</p>
                     </note>
